Assignment 1:

1. What is python ? What are the ways to install python in your PC ?

Answer- Python:

Python is an interpreted, object-oriented, high-level programming language with dynamic semantics.
Python's simple, easy to learn syntax emphasizes readability and therefore reduces the cost of program maintenance.
Python supports modules and packages, which encourages program modularity and code reuse.
Created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991, Python's design philosophy emphasizes code readability with its notable use of significant whitespace.

Filename extensions: .py,.pyi,.pyc,.pyd,.pyo (prior to 3.5),.pyw,.pyz (since 3.5)

Python can be used for things like: Back end (or server-side) web and mobile app development.

----Ways to install python in your PC:--

1.Python Installer:
From its official website you can download python version which is required for you.
https://www.python.org

2. Anaconda:
https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual
Download the anaconda .exe file and install the anaconda tool into your system.After installing it will provide you the anaconda Prompt and anaconda navigator for your use in system.
Use the anaconda navigator for learning the python and python development it has many other libraries.

3. Pycharm:
https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm




Que2.-What are code environments? Types.

Answer:-

Code Environment:-
coding environments are the environments where we can write the codes and where compilation is performed and in that only we can get the output.

Types:-

1. Text Editors

Eg: Notepad,Visual studio code

2. Integrated Development Environment(IDE)

Eg: Pycharm and Spyder

3. Notebook Environment

Eg: Jupyter
